Code preview of the table States

USE DATABASECOUNTRYHL
go

IF EXISTS (SELECT 1
FROM SYS.SYSREFERENCES R JOIN SYS.SYSOBJECTS O ON (O.ID = R.CONSTID AND O.TYPE = 'F')
WHERE R.FKEYID = OBJECT_ID('STATES') AND O.NAME = 'FK_STATES_COUNTRY_F_COUNTRY')
ALTER TABLE STATES
DROP CONSTRAINT FK_STATES_COUNTRY_F_COUNTRY
go

IF EXISTS (SELECT 1
FROM SYSINDEXES
WHERE ID = OBJECT_ID('STATES')
AND NAME = 'COUNTRY_FOR_STATE_FK'
AND INDID > 0
AND INDID < 255)
DROP INDEX STATES.COUNTRY_FOR_STATE_FK
go

ALTER TABLE STATES
DROP CONSTRAINT PK_STATES
go

IF EXISTS (SELECT 1
FROM SYSOBJECTS
WHERE ID = OBJECT_ID('STATES')
AND TYPE = 'U')
DROP TABLE STATES
go

/*==============================================================*/
/* Table: STATES */
/*==============================================================*/
CREATE TABLE STATES (
STA_ID INT IDENTITY,
COU_ID INT NOT NULL,
STA_UF CHAR(2) NOT NULL,
STA_NAME VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
)
go

ALTER TABLE STATES
ADD CONSTRAINT PK_STATES PRIMARY KEY (STA_ID)
go

/*==============================================================*/
/* Index: COUNTRY_FOR_STATE_FK */
/*==============================================================*/




CREATE NONCLUSTERED INDEX COUNTRY_FOR_STATE_FK ON STATES (COU_ID ASC)
go

ALTER TABLE STATES
ADD CONSTRAINT FK_STATES_COUNTRY_F_COUNTRY FOREIGN KEY (COU_ID)
REFERENCES COUNTRY (COU_ID)
go
